Jeanette Chabalala, News24(Supplied by ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; At least 18 people have died and several others were injured after a minibus taxi hit the barrier of a bridge on the Msunduzi road in the Ximba area, KwaZulu-Natal paramedics said on Sunday.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said when emergency services arrived on scene, they found that several patients had succumbed to their injuries.Other patients died in hospital, he said.This is a developing story.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.